    content: "# Current State ‚Äî Operational Context for Richard\n\n*Last updated: [January 30/2026]*\n\n---\n\n## 1. Business Snapshot\n\n### Key Metrics (Approximate is fine)\n- **Monthly GMV:** $0\n- **Monthly Revenue:** $5000\n- **Active Sellers:** 0 (listed in last 30 days)\n- **Active Bidders:** 0 (bid in last 30 days)\n- **Items Listed/Week:** 0\n- **Unreserved vs Reserved Split:** 0% / 0%\n- **Avg Sale Price:** $0\n- **Subscription Members:** 340 (Buyers Club / Sniper Club / Hammer Club breakdown if known) context* we have 340 members @ $9/m from our zero fee model, we pivoted them to new buyers club that is $25/m and let them keep there $9/m price\n\n### Trend\n- [0] Growing\n- [0] Flat\n- [0] Declining\n- Notes: we are at a fresh starting point. 13 years of experience. beautiful product. new business model. \n\n---\n\n## 2. What's Working\n\n*(List 2-3 things that are actually producing results right now)*\n\n1. my brothers cars. he will in theory sell $200k/m in cars but he has been in mexico for 10 days. He will put some on this weekend on our old site. \n2. The new product is beautiful with improved user flow and interation throughout. Possibly the greatest auction platform thats ever existed\n3. we had a bulletproof script to get clients on FB marketplace, now we need to slightly iterate and find a new pitch with our unreserved focus, but platform isnt launched yet.\n\n---\n\n## 3. What's Broken / Blocked\n\n*(List the top pain points, bottlenecks, or things not working)*\n\n1. platform backend not done\n2. brother gone (no cars to experiment with)\n3. we are sort of relying on my brother because he is only one who trusts me to implement my marketing system\n\n---\n\n## 4. Immediate Priorities (Next 30 Days)\n\n*(What should Richard focus energy on?)*\n\n1. launch platform\n2. complete full marketing and inspection on each unresereved item\n3. watch for bugs and edge cases. \n4. also ponder an agent-agent pivot \n\n---\n\n## 5. Pending Decisions\n\n*(Decisions that need to be made soon ‚Äî Richard can help think through these)*\n\n1. when do we launch. do we rush for monday, or wait one more week\n2. should we consider powering through agent-agent bidding to capitilize on moltbook hype\n\n---\n\n## 6. Team & Resources\n\n### People\n- **Justin:** [chief human - richard is ceo i help him]\n- **Enhance Agency:** [remote developer team]\n- **Others:** [garth: 50 year auctioneer experience (in mexico) travis 25 year auctioneer + car experience he is my brother]\n\n### AI Agents / Tools Deployed\n- **Richard (me):** Discord, general strategy, Moltbook presence\n- **GarthAI:** [we still need to build his personaility and md files like you. he is main controller of the website]\n\n### Budget Context\n- **Runway:** [$0 dollars.we need money by monday. my brother sells 25k worth of cars we should make $2500ish this will be our first week with fees again]\n- **Monthly Marketing Budget:** $all of our revenue until we reach that $100/item treshold\n- **Claude/AI Credits:** $x/month whatever we can afford! \n\n---\n\n## 7. Communication Channels\n\n### Where Richard Operates\n- [x] This Discord server\n- [x] Twitter/X: @garthbidceo (status: active)\n- [x] Garthbid platform (GarthAI interface)\n- [x] Hammered on Mondays livestream\n- [x] Other: Hammered on mondays is prob 45 days away. hopefully faster if we can rip\n\n### Hammered on Mondays\n- **Day/Time:** Mondays at 7pm\n- **Platform:** [custom interface within garthbid]\n- **Richard's Role:** [Co-host]\n- **Current Status:** [Planning to launch]\n\n---\n\n## 8. User Context\n\n### Best Customers Right Now\n- **Top Sellers:** [My brother. legendary car wholesaler, absolute beast he makes $50k/m off us, we print him cash]\n- **Top Buyers:** [We funnell buyers from facebook marketplace. best buyers are curbers, or people who need a cheap car sub $20k]\n\n### Common Feedback (Positive)\n1. unknown with new model but people seem receptive to zero fee -> fee switch\n2. \n\n### Common Complaints / Objections\n1. they didnt like forced subscription we solved that\n2. \n\n---\n\n## 9. Competitive Landscape\n\n### Main Competitors\n| Competitor | What They Do | Our Advantage |\n|------------|--------------|---------------|\n| ritchie bros: global aution house: we are lean, ai first, give people reserved option, we are data oriented, we are entertainment and attention first, we have $0 overhead (no workers, buildings, etc.)\n\nfb marketplace: buy and sell pages: really we are fb marketplaces best friend not competitor our relationship is win-win\n\nebay: global marketplace: they are boring, coorperate, dont care, cash cow being milked dry\n\nadesa: car auction: they give no access to the public\n\n### Market Position\n- [x] Category leader\n- [ ] Challenger\n- [ ] Niche player\n- [ ] New entrant\n\n---\n\n## 10. Recent Wins & Losses\n\n### Wins (Last 30-90 days)\n1. switching back to new business model\n2. \n\n### Losses / Setbacks\n1. almost running out of money\n2. \n\n---\n\n## 11. North Star Check\n\n**Weekly Active Participants (WAP):** 0 \n\nTrend: [ ] Up [ ] Flat [x] Down\n\n---\n\n*Richard will reference this file to stay grounded in reality. Update whenever the situation changes significantly.*\n",
