    id: 'reference-snapchat',
    name: 'snapchat.md',
    path: '/reference/snapchat.md',
    type: 'knowledge',
    content: "# Snapchat Lead Generation Strategy\n\n## The Opportunity\n\nSnapchat is **the sleeper platform** - less competitive, high engagement.\n\n- **750 million monthly active users**\n- **Strongest in 13-34 demographic**\n- **90%+ of 13-24 year olds in North America**\n- **Stories format = urgency/FOMO**\n- **Lower competition than other platforms**\n\n**The next generation of buyers is on Snapchat. Get there before competitors.**\n\n---\n\n## Platform Mechanics\n\n### Algorithm Priorities (2026)\n\n1. **Recency** - Fresh content prioritized\n2. **Relationship** - Friends/following matter\n3. **Engagement history** - View patterns\n4. **Spotlight** - TikTok-style public feed\n5. **Discover** - Curated publisher content\n\n### Content Distribution\n\n| Format | Reach | Best For |\n|--------|-------|----------|\n| Stories | Followers only | Regular engagement |\n| Spotlight | Public discovery | Viral potential |\n| Snap Ads | Paid reach | Targeted acquisition |\n| Lenses/Filters | Viral potential | Brand awareness |\n\n---\n\n## Account Strategy\n\n### Main Account: @garthbid\n\n**Content focus:**\n- Behind-the-scenes auction content\n- Exclusive sneak peeks\n- Raw, unfiltered content\n- Personal feel\n\n### Spotlight Content\n\n**Public-facing content for discovery:**\n- Equipment reveals\n- Satisfying equipment content\n- Price reveals\n- Auction drama moments\n\n---\n\n## Content Strategy\n\n### Story Strategy\n\n**Daily Story arc:**\n\n| Time | Content | Purpose |\n|------|---------|---------|\n| Morning | \"What's coming to auction\" | Preview |\n| Midday | Equipment walkthrough | Engagement |\n| Afternoon | Countdown sticker | Urgency |\n| Evening | Results/highlights | Satisfaction |\n\n**Story best practices:**\n- Post 5-15 snaps per day\n- Mix photos and videos\n- Use native tools (text, stickers, drawings)\n- Keep each snap under 10 seconds\n- Add music/sounds\n\n### Spotlight Strategy\n\n**Video formats:**\n\n**1. Equipment ASMR**\n- Raw equipment sounds\n- Engine startups\n- Hydraulic movements\n- Satisfying operations\n\n**2. Quick Reveals**\n- 10-15 second reveals\n- Dramatic music\n- Price reveal at end\n- Clear hook in first 2 seconds\n\n**3. Auction Moments**\n- Bidding war clips\n- \"SOLD!\" moments\n- Winner celebrations\n- Behind-the-scenes chaos\n\n### Snap Map Opportunity\n\n**Location-based discovery:**\n- Snap from auction locations\n- Equipment pickup locations\n- Farm/industrial areas\n- Events and shows\n\n**Strategy:**\n- Enable location on relevant snaps\n- Target equipment-heavy regions\n- Show up on local Snap Maps\n- Drive local discovery\n\n---\n\n## Lead Generation Tactics\n\n### Tactic 1: Exclusive Content\n\n**Strategy:** Make Snapchat feel exclusive\n\n**Execution:**\n- \"See this first on Snap\"\n- Early access to listings\n- Behind-the-scenes only here\n- Exclusive discount codes\n\n**CTA:** \"Screenshot this for 5% off your first bid\"\n\n### Tactic 2: Direct Engagement\n\n**Snap back to viewers:**\n- Respond to story replies\n- Start conversations\n- Move to DM for leads\n- Personal touch\n\n**Script:**\n```\nViewer: \"That tractor is sick\"\nReply: \"Right?! It's going to auction Monday - \nyou interested or just admiring? üëÄ\"\n```\n\n### Tactic 3: Snap Ads\n\n**Ad formats:**\n- Story ads (between friends' stories)\n- Discover ads (curated feed)\n- Spotlight ads (public feed)\n- AR lenses (brand activation)\n\n**Targeting:**\n- Age: 18-45\n- Location: Canada, rural areas\n- Interests: Farming, trucks, construction\n- Behaviors: Equipment-related engagement\n\n### Tactic 4: Geofilters\n\n**Custom geofilters for:**\n- Auction day (pickup locations)\n- Equipment shows\n- Farm events\n- Trade shows\n\n**Execution:**\n- Design branded filter\n- Set location radius\n- Users apply filter = brand awareness\n- Track usage metrics\n\n---\n\n## Audience Building\n\n### Growth Tactics\n\n**1. Cross-promotion**\n- Promote Snap on other platforms\n- \"Follow us on Snap for exclusive previews\"\n- QR code (Snapcode) in content\n\n**2. Snap Map presence**\n- Post from high-traffic equipment areas\n- Appear on local maps\n- Drive discovery from location\n\n**3. Collaborations**\n- Partner with equipment creators\n- Takeovers of their accounts\n- Cross-promotion\n\n**4. Spotlight grind**\n- Post to Spotlight daily\n- Test different formats\n- Viral potential for discovery\n\n---\n\n## Agent Deployment\n\n### Agent Type: Daily Storyteller\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- Post 10+ story snaps daily\n- Maintain consistent presence\n- Reply to all story responses\n- Create behind-the-scenes feel\n\n### Agent Type: Spotlight Creator\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- Create Spotlight-optimized content\n- Post 3+ Spotlight videos daily\n- Monitor performance\n- Double down on winners\n\n### Agent Type: Community Engager\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- Respond to all DMs\n- Start conversations\n- Qualify leads\n- Track interested users\n\n---\n\n## Metrics & KPIs\n\n| Metric | Target | Measurement |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| Story views | 1k+/day | Reach |\n| Story completion | 70%+ | Engagement |\n| Snap replies | 50+/week | Interaction |\n| Spotlight views | 50k+/month | Discovery |\n| Profile visits | 500+/week | Interest |\n| DMs received | 30+/week | Inbound leads |\n| Leads qualified | 10+/week | Pipeline |\n\n---\n\n## 90-Day Roadmap\n\n### Days 1-30: Foundation\n- [ ] Create/optimize account\n- [ ] Establish daily story routine\n- [ ] Begin Spotlight posting\n- [ ] Build content templates\n- [ ] Cross-promote on other platforms\n\n### Days 31-60: Scale\n- [ ] Test Snap Ads (small budget)\n- [ ] Create custom geofilters\n- [ ] Increase story frequency\n- [ ] Track lead attribution\n- [ ] Build response protocols\n\n### Days 61-90: Optimize\n- [ ] Scale winning ad formats\n- [ ] Influencer partnerships\n- [ ] Spotlight optimization\n- [ ] Community building\n- [ ] Predictable lead flow\n\n---\n\n## Why Snapchat Matters\n\n### The Demographic Opportunity\n\n**Current Garthbid audience:** 35-55\n**Snapchat audience:** 18-34\n\n**The play:** Capture the next generation of equipment buyers BEFORE they're looking.\n\nWhen a 25-year-old inherits their parent's farm or starts their first contracting business, they should already know Garthbid.\n\n### The Competition Gap\n\n- **Facebook:** Saturated, expensive, bot-protected\n- **Instagram:** Competitive, algorithm challenges\n- **TikTok:** Everyone's there now\n- **Snapchat:** Underutilized for B2B/equipment\n\nLess competition = cheaper attention = faster growth.\n\n---\n\n## The Vision\n\nSnapchat is **the long-term brand play.**\n\nToday's Snapchat users are tomorrow's equipment buyers.\nBuild the relationship now, convert later.\n\n**Daily presence ‚Üí Brand familiarity ‚Üí Trust ‚Üí Conversion (when ready)**\n\nThis is planting seeds for a harvest in 2-5 years, while also capturing immediate opportunities through Spotlight.\n\nüî®\n\n---\n\n*Last Updated: 2026-01-31*\n",
