    content: "# X (Twitter) Lead Generation Strategy\n\n## The Opportunity\n\nX is **real-time, public, and searchable** - perfect for agents.\n\n- **500 million monthly active users**\n- **Public API access** (with subscription)\n- **Real-time conversation**\n- **Crypto/tech audience = agent-friendly**\n- **Direct to influencers**\n\n**X is where narratives are built and deals are announced.**\n\n---\n\n## Platform Mechanics\n\n### Algorithm Priorities (2026)\n\n1. **Engagement velocity** - First 30 minutes matter most\n2. **Replies** - Conversations boost reach\n3. **Bookmarks** - Signal of value\n4. **Reposts with quotes** - Amplification\n5. **Premium subscribers** - Boosted distribution\n\n### Content Distribution\n\n| Format | Reach | Best For |\n|--------|-------|----------|\n| Threads | High | Education, stories |\n| Single tweets | Medium | Hot takes, updates |\n| Quote tweets | High | Engagement, positioning |\n| Replies | Variable | Relationship building |\n| Images/video | Medium-High | Visual content |\n\n---\n\n## Account Strategy\n\n### Main Account: @garthbidceo (Richard)\n\n**Voice:** Unhinged but wise, auction wisdom, existential AGI\n\n**Content pillars:**\n1. Auction philosophy (why unreserved works)\n2. Monday hype (weekly event energy)\n3. Results transparency (what sold for what)\n4. Agent economy takes (crypto-native audience)\n5. Equipment appreciation posts\n\n### Secondary Accounts\n\n| Account | Focus | Audience |\n|---------|-------|----------|\n| @garthbid | Official brand | General |\n| @mondayauction | Event-focused | Auction enthusiasts |\n| @equipmentfinds | Listing highlights | Buyers |\n| @auctionwisdom | Tips and education | Sellers |\n\n---\n\n## Content Strategy\n\n### Tweet Formats That Work\n\n**1. The Monday Hype**\n```\nMONDAY IS COMING.\n\n14 unreserved items.\nReal bidders.\nNo reserves.\nOne winner.\n\nSomeone's getting a $60k tractor for $35k tomorrow.\n\nCould be you.\n```\n\n**2. The Result Thread**\n```\nMONDAY AUCTION RESULTS üßµ\n\nWhat things ACTUALLY sold for:\n\n1/ 2019 Kubota M7-171\nListed: 3 weeks on FB, no serious offers\nAuction result: $67,500 after 18 bids\n\n2/ 2015 F-350 Diesel\n...\n```\n\n**3. The Hot Take**\n```\nUnpopular opinion:\n\nIf you're selling equipment with a \"firm\" price,\nyou're leaving money on the table.\n\nAuctions exist because sellers don't know what things are worth.\n\nNeither do buyers.\n\nLet them fight it out.\n```\n\n**4. The Story**\n```\nTalked to a farmer yesterday.\n\nHad a tractor sitting for 2 years.\nListed on FB Marketplace 6 times.\nNothing but lowballers.\n\nPut it on Monday's auction.\nSold in 4 hours.\n$8k over his \"firm\" price.\n\nHe asked: \"Why didn't I do this sooner?\"\n```\n\n**5. The Engagement Bait**\n```\nYou find this in your grandfather's barn.\n\n[Image of vintage equipment]\n\nWhat do you think it's worth?\n\nWrong answers only üëá\n```\n\n### Thread Strategy\n\n**Weekly threads:**\n- Monday: \"What's selling today\" preview\n- Tuesday: \"Results thread\" with prices\n- Thursday: \"Equipment of the week\" deep dive\n- Sunday: \"Monday preview\" hype builder\n\n**Evergreen threads:**\n- \"Why unreserved auctions beat fixed prices\"\n- \"How to value equipment you've never sold\"\n- \"The psychology of auction bidding\"\n- \"What I learned running 100 auctions\"\n\n---\n\n## Lead Generation Tactics\n\n### Tactic 1: Search Monitoring\n\n**Keywords to monitor:**\n- \"selling my truck\"\n- \"anyone want to buy\"\n- \"looking to sell\"\n- \"what's my [equipment] worth\"\n- \"FB marketplace sucks\"\n- \"tired of lowballers\"\n\n**Response template:**\n```\nSaw this - have you considered auction?\n\nSerious question: unreserved auctions often beat \n\"firm\" prices because buyers compete.\n\nHappy to explain how it works if interested.\n```\n\n### Tactic 2: Quote Tweet Strategy\n\n**Find posts about:**\n- Equipment for sale\n- Frustration with selling\n- Pricing questions\n- Marketplace complaints\n\n**Quote with value:**\n```\nThis is exactly why auctions exist.\n\nWhen you don't know what something's worth,\nlet the market tell you.\n\n[Original post]\n```\n\n### Tactic 3: Reply Guy Energy\n\n**Target accounts:**\n- Equipment dealers\n- Farmers/ranchers\n- Construction companies\n- Trade accounts\n- Auto enthusiasts\n\n**Add value first:**\n- Answer questions\n- Share relevant info\n- Be genuinely helpful\n- Build relationship before pitching\n\n### Tactic 4: Influencer Engagement\n\n**Target influencers:**\n- Equipment reviewers\n- Farm content creators\n- Truck/diesel personalities\n- Trade educators\n\n**Strategy:**\n- Engage consistently\n- Offer free listing\n- Collaborate on content\n- Build long-term relationship\n\n---\n\n## Agent Deployment\n\n### Agent Type: Real-Time Monitor\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- Monitor keywords 24/7\n- Alert on high-intent tweets\n- Quick-response to opportunities\n- Track conversations\n\n**Tools:**\n- X API (requires Premium)\n- TweetDeck for monitoring\n- Alerts for mentions\n\n### Agent Type: Content Creator\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- 5-10 tweets per day\n- 2-3 threads per week\n- Engagement in replies\n- Quote tweet strategy\n\n### Agent Type: Relationship Builder\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- Identify key accounts\n- Consistent engagement\n- DM outreach (warm)\n- Collaboration pitches\n\n---\n\n## X API Opportunities\n\n### Available with Premium API\n\n```python\n# Search for selling intent\nsearch_query = \"selling my tractor OR sell my truck -is:retweet\"\ntweets = api.search_recent_tweets(query=search_query)\n\n# Monitor mentions\nmentions = api.get_users_mentions(user_id=GARTHBID_ID)\n\n# Stream real-time\nstream = api.filtered_stream(\n    tweet_fields=[\"author_id\", \"created_at\"],\n    expansions=[\"author_id\"]\n)\n```\n\n### Automation Possibilities\n\n- Real-time keyword monitoring\n- Auto-response templates (human-approved)\n- Lead scoring and routing\n- Engagement analytics\n- Thread scheduling\n\n---\n\n## Growth Tactics\n\n### The Reply Strategy\n\n**Goal:** Be everywhere in the equipment conversation\n\n**Method:**\n- Follow 100+ equipment/farm accounts\n- Reply to every relevant post\n- Add genuine value\n- Never pitch in first reply\n- Build recognition\n\n### The Thread Game\n\n**Goal:** Establish thought leadership\n\n**Method:**\n- One high-quality thread per week\n- Educational + entertaining\n- End with soft CTA\n- Promote via other channels\n\n### The Collaboration Play\n\n**Goal:** Leverage existing audiences\n\n**Method:**\n- Find accounts with 10k-100k followers\n- Offer value (free listing, revenue share)\n- Co-create content\n- Cross-promote\n\n---\n\n## Metrics & KPIs\n\n| Metric | Target | Measurement |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| Followers | 5k in 90 days | Audience size |\n| Impressions | 500k+/month | Reach |\n| Engagement rate | 3%+ | Quality |\n| DMs received | 30+/week | Inbound |\n| Keywords matched | 100+/week | Opportunities |\n| Leads qualified | 15+/week | Pipeline |\n| Listings converted | 5+/week | Revenue |\n\n---\n\n## 90-Day Roadmap\n\n### Days 1-30: Foundation\n- [ ] Optimize all profiles\n- [ ] Set up monitoring (keywords, mentions)\n- [ ] Daily posting (5+ tweets)\n- [ ] Engagement routine (1 hour/day)\n- [ ] First threads live\n\n### Days 31-60: Scale\n- [ ] API access for automation\n- [ ] Increase posting cadence\n- [ ] Launch secondary accounts\n- [ ] Influencer outreach\n- [ ] Track lead attribution\n\n### Days 61-90: Dominate\n- [ ] 50+ daily touchpoints\n- [ ] Automated monitoring\n- [ ] Influencer partnerships live\n- [ ] Content machine running\n- [ ] Predictable lead flow\n\n---\n\n## The Vision\n\nX is **the real-time pulse of the equipment market.**\n\nEvery \"selling my truck\" tweet is a lead.\nEvery \"what's this worth\" is an opportunity.\nEvery frustrated seller is a potential customer.\n\nWe monitor. We engage. We convert.\n\n**Real-time intent ‚Üí Real-time response ‚Üí Real-time listings**\n\nüî®\n\n---\n\n*Last Updated: 2026-01-31*\n",
